-- Citigroup may raise $616 million with Brazil card sale
-- 
-- Tue Jan 15, 2008 2:15pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/15/us-citigroup-brazil-sale-idUSN1553175220080115

 

 SAO PAULO  (Reuters) - Citigroup Inc ( C.N ) may raise 1.08 billion reais ($616.1 million) with the sale of a stake in its Brazilian credit card unit, Redecard RDCD3.SA, according to a prospectus of the sale filed on Tuesday. 

 Citigroup plans to sell 41.13 million shares of Redecard, which traded at 26.25 reais Tuesday. Earlier Tuesday, the U.S. bank said it plans to raise $14.5 billion from a group of investors to help shore up its balance sheet after taking huge write-down for losses related to a slump in credit markets. ($1 = 1.753 Brazilian reais) (Reporting by  Elzio Barreto ; Editing by Jeffrey Benkoe)